ce, Germany, Hong Kong, Hungary, South Korea, Sweden and the UK, show how welfare could support people’s caring and working lives. This book forms a prescient examination of how productivist thinking underpins regimes and impacts women’s welfare, care and work in both the East and West.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aChung, Heejung, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaasch, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKühner, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYu, Sam, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311119677040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447357728423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447357728/original  a978-3-11-119677-0  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles